{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f114931d-fa42-468b-821c-a537248b44a5","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nAfter updating, run:\n```bash\ndotnet restore\ndotnet build\n```\n\nAlso check for any NuGet packages targeting `net10.0` (e.g., `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.Extensions.*`) and update them to their .NET 11-compatible versions via `dotnet outdated` or manually in the `.csproj`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"16af223c-cbcd-4971-a9d8-a827b4db3756","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no need to search their codebase since they've described the files. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":303,"requestId":"D832:16FA92:5F92A30:68D24FF:69F162A2"},"id":"8870b96e-68ab-44f9-ac22-8568a93ea1c0","timestamp":"2026-04-29T01:45:12.368Z","parentId":"67582fb0-54b4-4a66-8ee2-afa54caeef70"}
